In the Matter of WEIBEL BREWING CO., Bankrupt. In re CROWN CORK & SEAL CO., Appellant. No. 65. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 2, 1936. Arthur Klein, Robert J. Woodruff, and Charles Albom, all of New Haven, Conn., for appellant. Stoddard, Wetzler, Persky & Eagan, of New Haven, Conn. (Harold C. V. Eagan and S. Fred Wetzler, both of New Haven, Conn., of counsel), for appellee.

Before L. HAND, SWAN, and AUGUSTUS N. HAND, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed on the authority of In re Day & Co., 178 F. 545 (C.C.A.2); In re Stradley & Co. (D.C.) 187 F. 285.
